-------------
None. The upstream source tree under ./upstream/ is kept verbatim to make
it obvious — including to external reviewers — that we are not tweaking
the backend to favour any specific gateway.

CI metadata files that are only relevant to the upstream project
(`.github/`, `.goreleaser.yaml`, `.codecov.yml`, `.golangci.yaml`,
`kustomize/`, `examples/`, upstream `Dockerfile`, upstream `Makefile`)
were omitted from the vendored tree because they have no effect on the
benchmark backend itself.
